From f11c240bb0ab18a362808371f4f806af36e15dd2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vinod Koul <vinod.koul@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2015 23:55:26 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1621/2508] ASoC: Intel: use CONFIG_SND_SOC for intel boards

commit 56e7366e43ca676dd28f0e91240a579ad41e9b71 upstream

The Intel boards directory was under CONFIG_SND_SOC_INTEL_SST so the
machines which don't need these were not allowed to be
selected/compiled without enabling this symbol The machine should be
allowed to selected by ASoC and then they should select rest of
symbols required

Reported-by: Michele Curti <michele.curti@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Vinod Koul <vinod.koul@intel.com>
Acked-by: Liam Girdwood <liam.r.girdwood@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>
---
 sound/soc/intel/Makefile |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/intel/Makefile b/sound/soc/intel/Makefile
index 2972699..2b45435 100644
--- a/sound/soc/intel/Makefile
+++ b/sound/soc/intel/Makefile
@@ -8,4 +8,4 @@ obj-$(CONFIG_SND_SST_MFLD_PLATFORM) += atom/
 obj-$(CONFIG_SND_SOC_INTEL_SKYLAKE) += skylake/
 
 # Machine support
-obj-$(CONFIG_SND_SOC_INTEL_SST) += boards/
+obj-$(CONFIG_SND_SOC) += boards/
